# Sales Dashboard - Power BI & PPT Summary

## 📊 Project Overview
This project demonstrates an **interactive Sales Dashboard** built using **Power BI**.  
It visualizes key sales insights, customer trends, and performance metrics.  
Additionally, a **PowerPoint summary** has been created to present the insights in a professional format.

## 🚀 Key Features
- **Total Sales**: 2.33M  
- **Maximum Profit**: 8.40K  
- **Average Discount**: 0.16  
- **Total Quantity Sold**: 39K  

### Visual Insights:
- Sales by **Sub-Category** and **Year (2020–2023 trends)**  
- Sales distribution by **Category (Furniture, Technology, Office Supplies)**  
- Top **Customers by Sales Contribution**  
- Time-series trends (Sales by Day & Month)  

## 📂 Repository Structure
- `Sales_Dashboard_Summary_Pro.pptx` → Final presentation with visual highlights  
- `Sales_Dashboard_Summary_With_Image.pptx` → Presentation including the Power BI dashboard image  
- `Sales_Dashboard_Summary.pptx` → Initial summary presentation without visuals  
- `Screenshot.png` → Snapshot of the interactive dashboard (Power BI)  

## 🛠️ Tools Used
- **Power BI** → Dashboard creation & visualization  
- **Python (python-pptx)** → Automated PowerPoint generation  
- **MS PowerPoint** → Professional presentation formatting  

## 📌 How to Use
1. Open the Power BI file (`.pbix`) if available to explore the interactive dashboard.  
2. Review the **PPT summaries** for management-ready insights.  
3. Clone the repository and adapt the code for your own dashboard automation.

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/sales-dashboard.git
cd sales-dashboard
